caption:
Bubble tea : une boisson à la mode ! 🧋

Pourquoi la faire au Thermomix®? 
Simplement parce qu’il y a la recette sur Cookidoo® et c’est plus facile de la suivre. 

Le thé aux perles, aussi appelé zenzou, boba ou thé aux bulles de l'anglais bubble tea, est une boisson originaire de Taïwan. 
C'est un mélange de thé froid ou chaud et de lait, parfumé de diverses saveurs et additionné de boules noires de tapioca, qui donnent son nom au thé aux perles.

Dans cette recette anglaise il y a du thé noir, du sucre brun, des perles blanches de tapioca, des glaçons et c’est tout.

Qui a déjà testé ? 

FRANCHEMENT ÇA VAUT LA PEINE DE GOÛTER !

C’est rafraîchissant et le goût du thé noir est sublimé!

🍑BenGong’s Tea 
📍UBC Vancouver 

Peach Oolong milk tea is my all-time fav bbt flavour so I was soo excited when I saw that BenGong’s had it 🤩 

First time trying this place and they have some unique toppings + flavours (i got peach jelly in my bbt!) HOWEVER. I spent a total of $10 on ONE BUBBLETEA... sooo although it is rlly good, the price is kinda wack🥴 
Fun fact: I love peach flavoured foods but I’m allergic to the actual fruit 😳 

Overall rating: 3.5/5🌟 i love the peach oolong but its definitely on the boujier side.

has a new feed ✉️

> hello everyone, i hope you are doing alright! even though most of you are only now seeing my account haha.. this is a redo of my archived “new feed post” because i am indecisive - whoops - but here is the final theme ✨

> thank you to those who stuck around during my short break. I needed to get my mind off of posting + browsing a lot of insta for a few days. my sleep schedule has been a mess since february and my motivation level’s been fluctuating w/distractions, so it was needed.

> if you are interested, my plan + goals for my study account and feed are:
• a plain and simple setup that makes me feel calm
• include some skincare because they’re important and pretty (lol)
not feeling obligated to imitate popular accounts
• use instagram as a healthy outlet and hobby
share some of my stationery

> if you are still reading, that’s nice :) i hope you enjoy this new beginning amid my indecisiveness and are motivated by it!

milk tea soufflé pancake w/ boba & brown sugar milk tea syrup (#gifted) // we were so excited when @by_bobabae reached out to us to try their DIY boba kit, but knowing us of course we couldn’t be satisfied with just your average boba drink! Hence this creation - a lightly and fluffy milk tea flavored soufflé pancake topped with boba pearls and brown sugar boba syrup. Sugar overload? Maybe, but wow what a fun fusion for any boba lover’s breakfast! 

In case you’re not as adventurous as we are, the DIY kit (serves 4, starts at $27.95) comes with everything you need to whip up some quick bubble tea drinks at home - big straws, tea bags, boba packets, flavored creamer (we got ube, matcha, and regular), and syrup packets that make it easy for you to control the sweetness level to taste. Super easy, and perfect for anyone who doesn’t have easy access to boba shops nearby.

@yifangtea.sg Yifang Taiwan Fruit Tea serves refreshing, 100% made in Taiwan fruit tea using freshly-picked tea leaves and the best seasonal fruits from selected regions in Taiwan. With an understanding of tradition, craftsmanship and the simple joys of life, Yifang Taiwan Fruit Tea continues to spread grandmother Yoshiko’s legacy all over the world. There are currently 1,500 outlets across Asia, North America and Europe. 

Now you can get your fruit tea fix at their newest outlets at Shell Station @ Bukit Batok Nature Park and Shell Station @ Sengkang. With their latest grab-and-go options at Shell petrol stations, you can expect more outlets coming to you in the heartlands.
Yifang Fruit Tea, a cup of premium mountain tea mixed with delicious pineapple jam, tangy passionfruit, and zesty lemon, apple and orange slices – for a “huat” and fruit kick with plenty of “ong lai”!
Ginger Lemon Tea, Longan & Jujube Tea and Pearl Ginger Black Tea Latte from the Traditional Taste Series that even grandparents and parents love
Songboling Mountain Tea, Lugu Oolong Tea that come in hot and cold options to aid digestion and cleanse the palate after a heavy reunion meal

BOBAUP! @bobaupseattle Have you tried self serve boba before? 

Last night we went out for dinner after my sisters soccer game and right next to the place we were gonna eat at was a self serve boba place! So you know I HAD TO GO! I’ve been meaning to go to a self serve boba place before and this was finally my chance! It was on the Ave near UW Seattle and normally I’m not by there all the time so it was an opportunity I had to try! 

You got to pick the size of your drink either a small, regular, or jumbo! And I chose a regular 

Then you can pick your toppings and and drink flavor and you can choose how much toppings you can put!! So you know I put a LOT OF BOBA! It was such a fun experience to see all the flavors they had and just creating my own drink! 

For my drink I got taro flavor with boba and pudding!

✨TP Tea: New and limited Grapefruit Series - starting March 10th! ✨

With the spring season fast approaching, @tptea.on will be launching their new and limited Grapefruit Series!! Both drinks are made from fresh grapefruit and ingredients to ensure refreshing flavours and quality drinks 🥰 Also how pretty are these drinks tho??? 🥺

Grapefruit Series includes two drinks:
🧋Grapefruit Iced Tea with Aloe (less ice, 50% sugar) - freshly squeezed grapefruit juice mixed with black tea, resulting in the perfect balance between sweet flavours and subtle hints of bitterness. Finished off with fresh grapefruit slices and aloe vera which was so so good 😍

🧋Pink Salt Cheese Crema Grapefruit Tea (less ice, 50% sugar) - fresh grapefruit blended with jasmine green tea. There is a layer of creamy cheese foam, finished with a sprinkle of sea salt, which adds a subtle flavour of saltiness! 

The new series will only be available for a limited time so make sure to grab some while supplies last! 

Thank you @tptea.on for having us and shoutout to the Commerce Gate location for the amazing hospitality and giving us an extra drink 🥺💕 #tpteaontario

📍District Tea // San Francisco (Mission District) - part 2: drinks🧋

OVERALL RATING: ★ ★ ★ ★.5/☆

⇨ Oolong Milk Tea with boba (left) 4/5☆
⇨ Hong Kong Milk Tea (right) 4.5/5☆

If you’re a big tea drinker, this is the place for you🫖!! The teas were very strong in both of my drinks! 

OOLONG: I love drinking oolong tea but this drink was so strong it took me awhile to get used to it. Once I did, it was addicting for me! Overall, the boba itself was good- sweet and chewy!!
-
HK: This is District Tea’s #1 drink! The tea was super strong and a bit sweet at first, but after some of the ice melted, it was the perfect drink! I bought the drink for my dad (who’s from Hong Kong) and he said it was good! :D
-
I’ll definitely be coming back to try District Tea’s other unique drinks and flavors! They have so many different drinks: milk teas, fruit teas, matcha drinks, sexy drinks (chamoy or coconut milk mixed drinks), and even ice cream floats!🤯 One that caught my eye and that I’ll definitely be getting next time is their milk tea float, using vanilla ice cream from Mitchell’s!🍦x🧋

** For reference, both drinks were ordered with regular sugar and ice **

Bubblewink is coming along!

Here is our final version of our tea bags that was sent off to our supplier for printing!
•
We’re making it easy to brew your bubble tea at home by putting pre-measured whole leaf tea into pyramid bags which means no measuring needed and no straining!  Just add one bag to 8 ounces of hot water and simply remove it once steeped. 
We also opted for individually wrapped teas to preserve freshness, bubble tea you make is as delicious as the last!  Our starter kits are going to come with four each of these teas: Assam Black Tea and Jasmine Green Tea.

BTS x SOPE x BOBAPOP

Announcement #2: introducing Suga 'Lil Meow Meow', a drink inspired by BTS's Suga that is dark, bold and floral. Available STARTING this upcoming BTS weekend (Saturday 3/13 & Sunday 3/14)!

Lil Meow Meow starts with our Darling Milk tea, which uses Darjeeling tea or frequently known as the "Champagne of teas," which has a musky-sweet tasting note similar to muscat wine and a strong flavor profile between a Black Ceylon tea and an Oolong tea. Next we top it with an in-house dark roasted coffee ☕ milk foam. As a finishing touch, we add our signature black pearls (boba) for a drink that is strong and bold in the beginning, then finishes to a subtle floral sweetness. 

Shout out to @dmvbtsevents team for organizing and decorating. Also shout out to @sweetsbycaroline with her super cute & delicious BT21 macarons, which a limited quantities of box sets will be available for purchase during the BTS weekend!

caption:
📍&Tea Yucha, Rotterdam

WAT EEN AANRADER! Wij zijn helemaal weg van &Tea Yucha! Vanaf het moment dat we binnen kwamen, kwamen wij terecht in een hippe tent. Overal decoraties, een hele fijne sfeer al met al. Het assortiment is behoorlijk groot en je kan zelf het percentage ijs en de zoetheid aanpassen naar wat het beste past bij jou! Bij het bestellen werd ook alles goed en helder uitgelegd en kregen we te horen dat bepaalde drankjes van zichzelf een bepaalde zoetheid hebben en niet aan te passen is. Wij geven het cafe zelf en de service een 9.5/10 ✨ 

De berry power tea is een heerlijk fruitig en verfrissend drankje waarbij ook echt rood fruit (aardbeien en bessen) is toegevoegd in het drankje! Het coole aan &Tea Yucha is dat je de zoetheid en het ijs kan aanpassen. Voor de berry power hebben we gekozen voor 50% zoet en 100% ice (ookal is het nog even winter 😉) Het drankje is lekker zoet en echt heerlijk verfrissend, ik heb vaak dat ik een drankje te zoet vind en het daardoor niet op krijg bij de berry power had ik daar totaal geen last van! Ik heb geen popping genomen voor de berry power omdat er al fruit in zat. Al met al is de berry power een grote aanrader als je van een niet te zoet drankje houdt en een fancy soort ice tea zoekt. De prijs van dit drankje is €5,50 voor een Large. Berry power krijgt een 8/10✨

De Matcha On The Wall heeft een standaard zoetheid van 50% die je niet kan aanpassen. De standaard topping die hierin gaat zijn Red Beans (en ja je leest het goed, echte rode bonen!). Deze kun je wel veranderen als je dat wilt, samen met de hoeveelheid ijs. De consistentie van de melk is bijzonder goed, de matcha smaak is ongelofelijk lekker en niet overheersend, zonder de topping al een dikke aanrader. Daarnaast zijn de rode bonen ongelofelijk smaakvol en ze passen makkelijk door je rietje heen. Bij het stuk bijten proef je gelijk de rode bonen en hun unieke smaak! Deze topper is te halen voor €5,29 En we geven hem een 9/10⭐️

Als je in de buurt bent dan raden we het zeker aan om langs te gaan bij &Tea Yucha! Wij kunnen in ieder geval niet wachten om nog meer drankjes van het menu te proberen⭐️

First restaurant to dine in since, dinning rooms reopened! It's been awhile with midterms coming up but finally got a day of relaxation 😌

I hadn't tired @amiteasagehill @amiteacanada yet nor a Beef Bánh Mì so I stopped by on my way home! The subs were amazing we got the beef and pork. The beef was a little spicy which I wasn't expecting but overall amazing taste! My favourite was the sauce but it was also pretty messy with it falling onto the table every single second 😂 and the bubble tea, I loved it, got the Lychee Milk Tea and the Rose Milk Tea. I hadn't had a good Lychee Milk Tea and the one here met my expectations, no loss of flavour, tastes just like a lychee and the Rose tasted exactly how it should be bitterness of the tea combined with rose and it's not too sweet. The food and drinks were amazing though the experience was a little off with the short table and trying to eat a sub without getting sauce all over myself. 😅

Tan Cha // Doraville // tea taster 1

Uji Green milk tea w/ tiramisu foam & caramel boba

🍵Tea: 10/10 guys.. this tea tasted so good!! The jasmine green taste was super strong and it almost just tasted like a clear tea?? Def wouldn’t recommend if you like creamier milk teas. The taste for this one was almost like a mixture between a milk tea and a clear tea? Haha it’s definitely not your typical green milk tea but I loved it bc the tea taste was so strong!! 

🍵Boba: 8/10 taste was good, their boba is always just a little too mushy(?) for me bc I prefer chewier boba but still good

🍵Sweetness: below average — I usually get less sugar here but I think I could go full sugar for this drink!

🍵Overall: 10/10 would recommend to anyone who likes strong tea flavors!! I’ve tried the ceylon and roasted oolong milk teas and the tea taste was never strong enough for me so I really liked this one

Minuman teh yang pertama kali ada di Taiwan sekarang udah ada di Semarang 😱😱😱

Berlokasi di kawasan kota lama tepatnya di Jl Kepodang bikin aktivitas jalan-jalan sore kalian makin kece 😎😎😎

Varian teh disini macem2, ada black tea, oolong tea, green tea, jade tea, dan milk tea yang divariasi sama macem2 rasa dan topping. Level gula dan es batunya juga bisa disesuikan dari 0%-100%. Apalagi cup nya, duh geemmeesss dan bisa kalian pilih sendiri mau warna yang apa.

Tadi kita nyobain menu Bubble Oolong Milk Tea. Rasa oolong tea nya wangi banget, ada pahit2nya, dan bubblenya kenyel banget 🤤🤤

Don’t want to line up for an hour for machi machi? 😂 Everyone was saying how they wouldn’t line up for 2 hours on my last post, but man lining up is better than staying home these days right?! hahaha anyway, CHECK OUT this spot on the bottom floor of Aberdeen Square! They feature in-store brewed oolong tea 🍵 and this new drink! Super convenient location and my go-to study spot! Give them some support!

📸:
$7.95 • Soy Oolong Snow Tea 🍡
$5.50 • Oolong Milk Tea with pearls 

Their mochi drink is actually about the same if not better than the machi machi one imo. They use a soy milk base instead and the mochi texture is more authentic👌They have different concepts at the end of the day though and the machi machi one imo was not that good, so it’s hard to compare the two. But for convenience and speed, this one sure wins! 🙌
【⭐️: 3.5/5】

Also can’t wait to try their purple yam cheese milk and berry much snow tea next time, sounds so good!

True or false, disposable paper cups are recyclable... 🥤
⁣
FALSE! They may look recyclable, but majority of them are NOT. 🙅🏻‍♀️ Although they are made largely of paper, disposable coffee cups are lined with plastic polyethylene, making the cups waterproof and able to contain liquid.⁣ 
⁣
The difficulty of recycling coffee cups is increased by the fact they are contaminated with our drinks.⁣ (When the sticky stuff doesn’t get rinsed out, it spills onto other items).
⁣
This means cups cannot be recycled at many standard recycling plants, and must instead be taken to special facilities which most people don’t. ⁣
⁣
Less than 1% of disposable paper cups ever end up being recycled!! ⁣

What can you do? Get a reusable cup or mug! Since most shops aren't accepting reusable cups, try making your favourite drinks at home when you can ☕️

Tag someone who needs to know this!

I give you....the golden lava smoothie from @chatimecanada

This drink was all over my feed. It's as if people were trying to tempt me into buying it. Well it worked people. I succumbed to the pressure and I got the dang drink. Ya happy now? I hope so 😅

Now. My review. It was...interesting. it was a very unique experience in a cup. At first the egg yolk was a bit overpowering. But then once it started to mix with the sesame smoothie and the crema on top, that's when things got juicy. I enjoyed it more when all the layers mixed together. Salty, Sweet , and Sesame!

It was a nice drink to try but I don't think I'll order it again. I'm always up for trying new things and enjoying the process. I'm an artist you know we love an adventure. But that don't mean I gotta go on the same adventure everytime if I don't really care for it. That's Neeky's 2 cents for ya!

Matcha Mango White Claw!

This drink was completely an experiment, and it turned out way better than I was expecting. I’ve made a couple of mango + matcha drinks before, including the Mango Matcha Fresca (from @thebobabook) and a Mango Matcha Latte, which is definitely a personal favorite! This drink is a super simple cocktail, using just 8 oz. of Mango White Claw and 1 tsp. of matcha, whisked with 2-3 oz. of cold water. If you’re someone who finds the flavor of matcha to be too strong or bitter, this is definitely a mellow, easy-sipping way to drink matcha. Next time, I think I’ll add a little bit of mango purée, but for a first attempt, I’m really pleased with how this turned out!

🆕 Boba Shop🧋

I stopped in to try @teaking.co today for their grand opening weekend! They have a buy one get one free bogo this weekend to celebrate their grand opening. The shop specializes in freshly brewed teas and house-made fruit syrups. We got the signature TK milk tea and high mountain oolong. Overall, I like the brewed tea taste in their drinks, but I definitely wish it was stronger. The milk teas are pretty milky and could use some extra tea strength. If you go there, no need to lower the sugar level as their drinks aren’t very sweet. Their boba is also the perfect amount of sweetness, and their sago is good too. 

📍Tea King, South Lake Union, Seattle, WA

Handcrafted Boba

We make our boba fresh using tapioca flour with no added additives or preservatives. Our boba is handled with care and precision from start to finish to insure perfect texture and flavor. Our Boba is served warm, soft, and with the right amount of chew. This is truly a labor of love and the end product is totally worth the extra effort. Say goodbye 👋 to rock 🪨 hard boba. QualiTEA matters!

At ProudLocalYYC we celebrate influential entrepreneurs in the city! Today we're spotlighting Elisa - founder of Thé Moon Tea House (@tmoon.ca) #, a bubble tea shop created for the love of tea and the moon. 

"Tea gives us energy but also calms us down. The moon has the same qualities, thus our name was created. We chose thé — french for tea — to celebrate the existence of bubble tea in Canada. After all, we all share one moon." 

ProudLocalYYC members save 10% so check out @tmoon.ca in Victoria Park. You'll enjoy premium ingredients (such as real fruit and cold press juice) made with natural sugar cane, and fresh mochi and pearls made every 4 hours! (It's totally drool-worthy 🤤)

Nasla som v @perma_market tapiokove perly, hneď som ich brala domov, že spravím domáci bubble tea. Perličky treba uvariť, trvá to asi 30min, musia byť celé priesvitné. Medzitým zmixujeme 350g ananásu, alebo iného ovocia s 200ml kokosového mlieka, pridáme sladidlo ak chceme. Perličky zlejeme z vody a prepláchneme studenou tak, aby boli úplne studené. Na dno pohára dáme perličky a zalejeme dzusikom. Nech sa páči, buble tea homemade. #bettylovescooking #pineapple #bubbletea #fruit #vegetarian #nogluten #tapioca #tapioka #tapiokoveperly #homemade #singluten #vitamin #kokosovemlieko #coconutmilk #homecook #juice

Oto nasza egzotyczna piękność, a do tego super fajna dziewczyna i Ambasadorka BubbleJoy: @11__thatblackgirl__11 ❤️. Pół Polka, pół Algierka, "Mamuśka" Naruto - pięknego Sfinksa, którego mieliście okazję już u nas widzieć, fanka tatuaży i kolczyków 😉! Kamila wygląda tutaj niemalże jak Maria Curie Skłodowska odkrywająca rad 😍... I co prawda nie ma na fotce nowego smaku miesiąca, ale jakbyście jeszcze nie wiedzieli to od wczoraj w BubbleJoy jest totalna "świeżynka", czyli EARLY SPRING!!! Już po pierwszym dniu wiadomo, że to Bubble Tea będzie HITEM 😁!!! Jest to mega mix banana, limonki i żurawiny, ale co najważniejsze to zazwyczaj banan występuje u nas w formie mlecznej herbaty, jednak tym razem jest przepysznym sokiem 🤤... Making milk tea at home is easier than you think! 😊

🥣 The 4 basic ingredients are:
👉🏼 Hot water 
👉🏼 A tea bag or loose leaf tea
👉🏼 Sugar (we suggest white sugar for green teas, and brown sugar for black tea)
👉🏼 Milk or your choice of creamer! 

Hope all of you treat yourself to a delicious cup of milk tea this weekend! 🧚🏻‍♀️

Welcome to #3 on my Top 5 places to eat in NYC, Yaya Tea. Here is ANOTHER spot I’ve been eating at for the last 6 years 😁Yaya tea is a small cafe that specializes in bubble tea & rice balls! But not just your regular milk tea with tapioca. No. They go the extra mile. They have so many different flavors of tea AND different flavor jellies!! Jellies such as mango, strawberry, lychee, yogurt and so much more! They also sell a variety of Japanese imported snacks. Talk about different huh 🤣 What REALLY makes them stand out is their hand made Onigiri, or what you might call it, Rice ball 🍙💕 You can get different kinds of rice balls such as Shrimp Tempura, chicken, crab, spam etc 😆 Make sure to stop by and experience so many different flavors of Japan, right here 🥰

⭐️8.5/10

Half & Half reminds me sooo much of my childhood, this was my og favorite boba spot! 😁 The iced milk drink is so good and honestly gives me so much nostalgia, the icey milk & honey boba pair perfectly together. The sesame smoothie was good as well, it wasn’t too sweet and reminded me a lot of soft serve! My faaavvv milk tea is always going to be green milk tea, and half & half did not disappoint with theirs. The tea flavor is really strong and goes perfectly with grass jelly and honey boba 🤤

📍OneZo, Irvine 
🍴Taro Fresh Milk w/ Taro Boba

✨ I've lived in the SGV and OC my whole life and never tried OneZo until recently when I walked past it and decided to stop by spontaneously — but I'm glad I did! Everyone say thank u to Nev for being hand model again — I think he’s getting really good at this HAHA😂 This drink really unlocked my boba cravings 😅 They had a pretty big menu here but mostly your standard drinks that you'd find at your typical boba shops. I did love that they had a variety of bobas though which makes their brand unique and adds a little something that other brands might not have. I saw that the Taro series was being advertised so decided to try the taro fresh milk with some taro boba as a topping. 

The drink itself was super pretty, with dark purple swirls of taro around the cup walls and white milk to fill in the rest of the cup. The purple taro boba pearls on the bottom made it extra aesthetic! Tbh it really is just taro milk once you shake it up, and quite a simple drink when it comes down to it. However, I did really enjoy it! Not too sweet and a light taste despite being a milky drink. The taro added a good flavor and I liked that I tasted little taro bits in the drink. The boba was really good— I wish there was more! It def had a taro taste/texture and I think it goes so well with this particular drink. Would def get this drink again next time! 

🖤

號稱為最邪惡美好滋味的黑糖珍珠鮮奶，本身Q彈有勁的小珍珠裹好裹滿手工熬煮黑糖醬充滿黑糖香與焦香的風味，粒徑較小黑糖醬跟珍珠體積的比例剛好可以讓每一顆珍珠咬起來感受到的黑糖香更加濃郁，加上滿杯奶香十足又滑順的光泉牛乳。﻿

🍙 MY OBSESSION WITH RICEBALL MOCHI DRINKS! 🍙
•
LOVE MOCHI? Have you ever had the experience of slurping up THICC, SILKY, LIQUID MOCHI YOGURT in a drink form? 
I am currently SUPER OBSESSED with @yogostvancouver_official ’s Riceball Milkshake and Rice Yogurt series! If you been following my stories, you know I normally get two once a week 😜 The feeling is so magical, especially if you love mochi, due to the interesting texture of mochi for their Riceball Milkshake series. Their Rice Yogurt is also really good and filling! Chomp’s In-depth Review Below! 🔽
•
𝐌𝐲 𝐓𝐨𝐩 𝟒 𝐅𝐚𝐯𝐨𝐮𝐫𝐢𝐭𝐞𝐬
📍HEY! I AM YOGOST!
⭐️ Peach RiceBall Milkshake 
🍓Strawberry Jelly RiceBall Milkshake 
🥭 Mango RiceBall Milkshake 
🌹Rose Yogurt
•
𝘎𝘦𝘯𝘦𝘳𝘢𝘭
First of all, they really mastered the balance of being not too sweet or sour (aftertaste)! The drinks here are normally very silky but doesn’t give that bloating or heavy feeling afterward. The RiceBall Milkshake Series is like a JOY PARTY for your tongue. I recommend 50% sugar as they’re light on the sweet here. The staff here are UNBELIEVABLY helpful EVERY SINGLE TIME.Always willing to entertain my questions and HONEST recommendations (first time I came, I asked about the pumpkin rice ball and they told me most customers say they don’t like as much.) I can tell they really care about your enjoyment for their drinks especially their manager. 

Peach RiceBall was my favourite and was on the slightly sweeter side. The peach taste goes really well with the riceball. Strawberry Jelly Riceball is a FUN packed drink with fresh strawberries pieces, jelly AND riceball. It feels kind of overloaded at times but it has all my favorite things in one! Mango Riceball is light, fresh and fruity. Good for a day when Im already semi full but need some fruit to balance my diet 😂 The Rose Yogurt has a fragrant taste but light. The purple rice that comes with is not too soft or hard, with some chew to it! 

Please note it takes 8-15 mins for them to make some of these drinks because they have a special processing method for their drink though IT IS WORTH THE WAIT. 

Have you tried the RICEBALL obsession yet? Which is your favorite? ⬇️⬇️⬇️
EMPLOYEE FAVORITES 💖: “Rose Milk Tea is my favorite drink 🌷because of its detox capability. It gets all the toxicity out of my body, like how I got my ex out of my life. 💀👩🏻”

It's getting chilly here in Melbourne! 🥶❄️ have you tried any of our proteins HOT yet? Because our Taro Milk Tea Protein tastes mighty fine with some hot oat milk! ♨️⁠
⁠
𝗛𝗢𝗧 𝗧𝗔𝗥𝗢 𝗣𝗥𝗢𝗧𝗘𝗜𝗡 𝗟𝗔𝗧𝗧𝗘 🍵⁠
⁠
1️⃣ Heat 250ml of your choice of milk in a mug for 1.5 - 2 minutes in a microwave⁠
⁠
2️⃣ In a separate shaker, shake up 100ml room temperature water with 1 scoop of taro milk tea protein until mixed ⁠
⁠
3️⃣ Poor your protein into the hot milk and stir to combine⁠
⁠
4️⃣ Get a cosy and enjoy! 🥰⁠
⁠
⚠️ Don't heat protein powder in the microwave as this will cause the whey to clump! Ensure you've shaken protein separately and mix with hot milk after.⁠
⁠
Let us know if you try this out! 🔥

Bubble Tea Blossom Pizza @ Pizza Hut

Let’s start off with the pizza crust itself. It was fluffy on the inside, crispy on the outside, mozzarella cheese within the stuff crust was gooey and nice. Overall, it was what we expected from Pizza Hut. Now comes the bubble tea pearls.

They were soft, sweet, not chewy and almost melts in the mouth. Was it weird? Definitely…. And with the marshmallow added, a whole new level of weirdness was made, creating an abominable mess, messing up what one would perceive as normal pizza.

I got a strawberry matcha latte, a honeycomb latte, and Einspanner, and all with boba, from Kamurocho in Pleasanton, CA.

Hands down this was one of the best matcha strawberry lattes I have had. The strawberry jam was house made and incredibly delicious. It really makes the drink what it is. It was definitely the best of the three. When I was done drinking it I felt a little sad that it was gone.

The honeycomb latte tasted like strong coffee with a hint of smooth honey sweetness.

The einspanner was very very strong coffee. If you want to wake up it'll help. The had a cream top with coco. 

We got all of these with boba, which the woman who was working there encouraged us not to get. She said the boba wasn't very good but we got it anyway. The boba was actually good though! I makes me feel like they have high standards there for quality. The boba was pleasantly sweet and on the chewy side. I enjoyed it!

The place itself is fairly new and unassuming in it's decor. It's not flashy but the drinks are incredible! The woman working there, I'm not sure if she was the owner, was so sweet and welcoming. She really cared how the drinks came out. She wanted us to go ahead and try them to make sure we liked them before we left. They also have shaved snow there but I didnt try any. Maybe next time, because I'll definitely be back!

Un posto che offre tante proposte particolari e innovative @crema_e_cioccolato_cbertone . Lo trovate su Glovo e Just Eat con il nome “C&C Food & Drink”.

Questo bar offre possibilità di fare colazione, pranzo, merenda e aperitivo! Tra le loro tante specialità troviamo assolutamente i bubble waffle dolci e salati, i bubble tea e le loro varie formule aperitivo. Ma davvero offrono un po’ di tutto!😍 
Anche un’ampia scelta di piatti vegan💚.

In foto📸:
1) bubble waffle con crema di caffè ☕️ con cristalli e gocce di cioccolato 🍫 fondente. L’impasto del waffle davvero morbido e gustoso. Caldo con tutte le gocce di cioccolato sciolte era davvero perfetto!🤩
2)bubble waffle con crema di pistacchio, panna e gocce di cioccolato 🍫. Anche questo molto buono. La qualità del pistacchio era ottima😋.
3) bubble waffle salato con falafel di ceci alla Luciana senza buccia cotte al forno, insalata 🥗, pomodori e maionese. Ma la particolarità di questo waffle è che l’impasto è vegan! Molto buono, quanto quello classico🤤. 
4) bubble tea ALCOLICI! Si avete letto bene🤩, ottimi per fare un aperitivo un po’ diverso dal solito. Con prosecco, mango 🥭 e mirtillo uno e l’altro con melograno e lici.😝 Se non lo avete mai fatto dovete assolutamente provarli!!🔥
5) iced coffee shekerato ☕️ con cacao. Rinfrescante, schiumoso e dal sapore deciso.

PREZZO: bubble waffle vegan con falafel (5,00€); con le creme (4,00€). Bubble tea non alcolici (3,00€). 

VOTO:9/10

🍵 Green Tea Skincare 🍵⁣
⁣
I have made a post like this on Centella before, but another one of my favorite ingredients in skincare is green tea.⁣
⁣
Green tea extract, often listed as cameillia sinesis in ingredient lists, is great for the skin. It's an antioxidant that works well for soothing the skin. It is also supposed to have anti-aging properties, although I can't speak for those effects myself (yet).⁣
⁣
This @annieswayofficialtaiwan mask is a great sheetmask for my fellow green tea lovers. It is super soothing and hydrating, while still keeping the oil production of the skin balanced. (The mask was kindly gifted to me by @saranghaeasianbeauty ).⁣
⁣

TABETAI 🌺.

Como os adelantaba en mi último reels, sigo descubriendo sitios en Donosti con opciones sin gluten.

Por aqui os dejo el bubble tea arcoíris de @tabetai_donostia , un take away muy chulo en pleno centro de la ciudad (al lado de la catedral del Buen Pastor) 🧋🧋🧋.

¿Pero exactamente que es? Es una bebida de origen taiwanés compuesta de una base de té a la que le añadimos el sabor que más nos guste y los topping que queramos. Esta muy rica y es muy refrescante ahora que se acerca el buen tiempo ☀️☀️☀️.

¿Y esas bolitas en la parte inferior? Son una mezcla de perlas de tapioca y popping bobas del sabor que elijas. Las popping bobas son unas bolitas rellenas de zumo que se explotan en la boca y la tapioca es una especie de gominola natural que preparan ellos mismos.  Una combinación brutal y muy adictiva 😍😍😍.

Si no te gusta el té , tienes opciones con café y chocolate para escoger. También tienes la opción de ponerle leche al té (Milk Tea) y de pedirlo frio o caliente. 

Ademas, toda la carta de bubble tea es sin gluten y su dueño es súper majo y te ayudará a elegir la mejor combinación ✌🏻✌🏻✌🏻.

Por último, pero no menos importante, no hay peligro de contaminación cruzada porque los bubble tea y los crepes japoneses( que de momento sólo los elabora con gluten )se preparan en espacios diferenciados.

📌 TABETAI
📍 Plaza Buen Pastor 12 (Donostia).

🗣¿Habeis probado los bubble tea? ¿Que os parece este descubrimiento ? Os leo 💕.

Feliz 5 de Marzo 💚.

Hello boba friends ❤️ In case you didn’t know, we closed the shop! It wasn’t an easy decision and I fought with these thoughts for quite a few months. Like “It’s been less than a year”, “what about your fans”, “wait what fans..” (you guys duh!), and “Oh no. Everyone’s going to think I’m a failure.” And yes I know now, that these thoughts are unwarranted. It’s so easy to hold on to the things we did wrong rather than allowing ourselves to celebrate our successes and our wins. So cheers 🎉 to opening up my dream shop and the courage to let go when I needed to, cheers 🎉 to actualizing an entire boba cookbook that came out 3 months ago, and last but not least, cheers🎉 to my never ending love for bubble tea. Let’s be clear - this is not a goodbye. We are just getting started.🔥
.
.
I am proud to say that I have pivoted my business to an online store at hellobobafriends.com. I have been hosting virtual bubble tea classes for almost a year now. And I am super excited for future boba runs rather than always making it myself. There's joy when you can pay for the things you love. 😂
.
.
P.S I promise to be more active on this account so please continue to cheer me on 🙌

caption:
@dribble.tea Hackney, London.

A new bubble tea spot in East Ldn? We luv to see it 🔥

I luckily got to try some teas from Dribble Tea aka (Dri)nk bu(bble) tea (🤯) - they’ve just recently opened up their own store (slide to see their aesthetic backdrop)!

I tried:
- Brown sugar milk tea
- Apple fruit tea with blueberry jelly
- Pina colada fruit tea with pineapple popping boba
- Passionfruit fruit tea with strawberry popping boba

(All at 50% sweetness and no ice)

The fruit teas were perfect, the taste of tea really came through unlike other brands - defo no bubbleology vibes over here (which is a good thing 😁) My favourite was the passionfruit tea for this reason! Also I loved how the boba actually popped and were flavourful!

The pina colada was so creamy and delish! I’ve never tried pineapple boba before so that was exciting too!

The tapioca in the brown sugar had a nice, chewy consistency - would have been even better if the tea taste was stronger (just my preference) my sister loved the brown sugar drink as it was.

Also, I have to mention their cup sizes because their large is actually hugeee - would be enough to share between two tbh

Overall, Dribble Tea offer a tasty, well-priced and unique menu - definitely worthy of trying out (I need to go get another fix of the apple fruit tea sooon 😋)

[Gifted]

Rating: 8.5/10

🦝 un Raccoon Parisien. 
La majorité des personnes qui croisent ma route font le même constat. Tu es vraiment une parisienne. Je ne comprend pas ce que vous entendez par là mais c'est le plus beau compliment que l'on puisse me faire. 

🦝 J'aime ma ville plus que n'importe quelle autre. Je suis tellement reconnaissante d'avoir eu cette chance de grandir dans le 15ème arrondissement. Toute ma famille s'est exilée loin d'ici et ça fait 10 ans environ que je suis seule ici. J'ai déjà songé à les rejoindre mais je ne pourrais jamais m'y résoudre.
Je ne sais pas ce que vous imaginez des parisiens mais je vais vous dire ce que moi je vois. 

🦝Je vois des gens qui se connaissent tous dans l'immeuble, je vois la gardienne de l'immeuble qui prend soin de cet escalier haussmannien et personne qui ne vote pour un ascenseur car nous aimons trop bâtiment.
🦝 Je vois des gens faire leurs courses au boucher, au primeur et tous les autres plutôt qu'au supermarché parce qu'on a besoin d'avoir confiance et nous recherchons la chaleur d'un sourire. 
🦝 Je vois des jeunes flâner sur les quais en riant aux éclats, des amoureux qui font une photo le pont des Arts après y avoir scellé leur amour par un cadenas. 
Je vois des bâtiments, des fontaines et des lampadaires magnifiques. 
🦝 je vois des orchestres improvisés, des gens qui dansent dans la rue, des artistes qui restent des heures devant une porte pour en percevoir les moindres détails. 
🦝 Je sens l'odeur de la boulangerie avant de partir au travail, je vois des rues vides presque introuvables et si belles. 
Je vois les premiers métros et le conducteur qui nous fait des blagues pour égayer notre journée. 

Vous allez trouver ça ridicule mais quand Notre Dame a brûlée, je faisais partie de ces gens qui pleuraient car ce n'est pas juste un bâtiment, c'est notre Histoire. 

🦝 Cette ville est un capharnaüm gigantesque, mais chaque cellule de mon corps perçoit la magie des siècles passés, l'histoire de cette ville et son évolution. 

Paris, tu es la plus belle, je t'aime. 

Et vous, vous êtes d'où ?

🥤 Tea Guys - Original Milk Tea

Finally went back to Amsterdam! And you already know I had to try out Tea Guys and their classic milk tea. I’ve been seeing their drinks all around Instagram, so I was very curious to see what they were like. Their shop is pretty nice and small, and you have a pretty wide menu variety of drinks and toppings, and the staff is very friendly. And from my experience, there’s a constant line outside. And I'll give them some extra positive points for the sign they have outside of their shop ☺️ 

Milk Tea consistency: 5/5 - I’m still not used to getting cold drinks again so I’m always wary when I don’t order something warm, but I was very pleasantly surprised. The milk tea was very silky and smooth.
Milk Tea taste: 4.5/5 - The milk tea was slightly on the sweeter side, but it had really nice hints of brown sugar.

Tapioca pearl consistency: 4.5/5 - The pearls were slightly on the harder side, but they still had a nice chew to them.
Tapioca pearl taste: 5/5 - The taste was very nice! There was a nice and subtle flavor of brown sugar syrup to the pearls that I always enjoy.
Pearl-Drink ratio: 4/5 - There were almost enough pearls for every sip of the drink

Balance: 4.7/5 - The drink was balanced pretty well. I think it was a drink that’s a bit sweeter than your usual classic boba milk tea, but if you’re like me and you enjoy sweet things, it will not be a problem at all.

Overall: 4.7/5 - I really enjoyed this drink and I was super glad to finally try it out after so long! The cup has their popular logo on it, and the boba seems to underline their name perfectly 

🥤 Medium size - 4.70 (worth it) 
🌸 Cup carrier - @snayz76
📍@teaguysnl

This is just my personal opinion on the Bubble tea, but I would be very glad to read about yours as well in the comments below ☺️.

Dear Calaistas,

Yes its Friday!!

Yuks yg jumatan ud ad rencana? 
Gmn si kalian selfcare and spend weekend kalian? 

Our fav drink this weekend is Taro milk tea 💕
Banyak yg tanya apa si bedanya Taro Milk Tea Calais dgn yg lain?
Well kalau kalian perhatikan, banyak Taro Milk Tea lainnya sebenarnya tdk menggunakan tea dan susu asli. Kebanyakan hanya powder dan susu powder non dairy loh. Tapi kalau di CalaisTea dan CalaisNu kt selalu menggunakan Taro powder with Jasmine Tea and Milk! 

Trus apa bedanya nih CalaisTea dan CalaisNu punya Taro Milk Tea? 
Well jawabannya adalah di Machiatto layernya! With CalaisNu kt tambahkan Machiatto layer spy rasa milktea nya lbh nendang lg 🎉💕🎊

So know your drink well!

Bubble tea at home!
When you’re going to the effort to prep your own pearls then you have to braise them for the best results. I made these brown sugar pearls to have in a peach iced tea, and it was great getting to have bubble tea homemade.
If you’ve never made pearls before but love them I would recommend buying 5 minute pearls from an Asian grocer and prepping them according to the recipe on the Jun & Tonic vlog!

it’s been a while since we’ve been to @cocoteaontario and we’ve definitely missed them 🥺🧋

brown sugar pearl milk tea (less ice, 50% sugar) - i’m actually not the biggest fan of brown sugar but something about coco’s brown sugar is sooo good 🙈 i like how the flavour is not too overwhelming cause i usually think brown sugar tastes like caramel most times which i don’t like. their brown sugar pearls are pretty sweet so i’d recommend getting 30% sugar cause this was still pretty sweet and my sweet tolerance is pretty high 🤣

jasmine milk tea with added tapioca (no ice, 30% sugar) - this was my sister’s first time trying this drink and it was pretty good!! 😍 shes been loving jasmine tea and this is one of her favourites now! she also didn’t realize you can get brown sugar pearls as a topping so next time she’ll pair this drink with brown sugar pearls instead of regular pearls cause she looooves brown sugar 🤣 

📷: brown sugar pearl milk tea (left) + jasmine milk tea with tapioca / price: $5.7 & $5 (+0.5 for tapioca)

📍Pearls, University of Reading
£

9/10 - I got the lychee with passion fruit boba and it was soo refreshing!! I asked for ice and it was so good! This would be perfect for summer☀️☀️ The passion fruit boboa bursts in your mouth striaght away ✨ I definately preferred this one compared to rania’s 👀

6/10- (just because you can’t really taste the caramel)-
I on the other hand got the caramel milk tea at 25% sugar🧋🧋. For someone that doesn’t really like any bitter drinks like tea or coffee, it’s actually quite lovely. Yet as a person that has never tried boba tea I would say get their fruit teas which are so refreshing to get used to boba and then start getting the milk teas!

 It is located on the university campus, it’s perfect to get during a break and the prices are reasonable!  This was our first time ordering but it did take a while to order due to the long queues ( maybe because it was Chinese New Year and there was a buy one get one free offer! ) 

🙋‍♀️🙋‍♂️ Have you guys tried the bubble tea on campus? If not what flavour would you get?

helloo friends! this is a non-art related post lols but i’d like to post more “slice of life” things :) i’m still working on my march bujo because i wasn’t too happy about my previous theme, hopefully it’ll be up by the end of this week or next week! and hehe this is my taro bubble tea from the other day, i’ve had too mnay during this quarantine but taro is my favourite flavour 🧋 it’s definitely a happy, comfort food hehe :)) 

rant of the day, read if only if you’d like: yesterday was quite a stressful day so i stayed off ig a bit! one of those days where you cry because theres so much i haven’t figured out yet and you’re scared you won’t be able to. tbh, looking at all these new responsibilities as i’m getting older has just been quite overwhelming, making me more anxious lately as well :,) but i know this is all new to me, so it’s okay to be scared. i know that i’m learning through this, i guess i just need to learn better ways to manage my time & stress because having a mind that worries often has really just taken away peace! 

i’m super blessed though to have friends who help me, pray for me and just make me feel like things will be okay. i also just appreciate all of you for staying with me :) my dms are always open if you want someone to talk to! i’m going to start allowing healthy energy and focus on what matters most; like doing more mindfulness, going on nature walks instead of staying in my room all day, and praying more :) i hope you all take care of yourselves even in the smallest of ways! being able to notice what isn’t working and choosing to have courage to change them one step at a time! life is unpredictable, and always changing, but we’re also growing one day at a time even when we can’t understand everything! ♡ i believe in you!

A new lockdown business has opened up right on our doorstep! Walsall finally has a smashed burger spot and we’re here for it!
Boba and buns have made waves with their elite combination of smashed beef burger patties and delicious boba drinks! 
We’ve had it quite a few times since they’ve opened but the el jalapeño jefe has to be one of our favourites! Filled with chilli jalapeño jam, nacho cheese and spicy Cheetos! 

I like to add their all new lamb truffle bacon to this beast of a burger, whereas my friend likes the burger without the Cheetos crunch. This burger spot is perfect and you can perfectly customise each order to your preference (I recommend extra jalapeño jam- it is amazing!!). The nacho cheese fries are a genius twist to a classic side. 

We’ve had a chance to try most of their drinks and the Ananas has to be the best addition to compliment the meal, although the Habibitea is a perfect after meal treat. We are planning a trip soon to try their new strawberry drink. 

You can order via Insta DM or give them a ring for collection, they’re super flexible with orders and have the best customer service! 10/10 for food and a friendly face!! 

A must try, which has definitely topped some of our other fave burger spots!! 

@bobaandbuns

The brown sugar pearl beverage frenzy was introduced by XFT Canada back on Dec 1, 2018 to Canadians. Two years later, we are very excited to have our first ever healthy bubble tea month!! 🎉 For the entire month of March, XFT Canada is partnering up with @simplybuckofficial and offering Canada’s first buckwheat milk bubble tea beverage!!!😍😍 We are extremely proud to have finally found that alternative non dairy milk that mesh well with our signature brown sugar pearls! 👀😋Drop by to any Greater Vancouver area stores starting March 5th and try it out!!🧋🙌🏻

Y por fin se conoció @ohtea_argentina 🤤😍
Si son amantes del té, tienen que sí o sí conocer oh tea. Tiene un menú muy variado para todos los gustos además de que no venden el típico té sino que es un té conocido como bubble tea, el cual contiene perlas de tapioca y lo hacen con leche y  ciertos de toppings de acuerdo al gusto🍵😍
El bubble tea es muy conocido en Asia y es una de sus bebidas favoritas gracias su dulzor que es parecido al azúcar de caña.

Ayer con mi amiga pedimos un bubble tea de oolong y un jugo de maracuya, naranja 🍊 y ananá 🍍 que para estas épocas de calor está increíble 🤤🤤🤤

Yo les recomiendo ir a eso de las 18 pm que baja el 🌞 para que así puedan disfrutar del clima en conjunto de su bebida PERO ojo al ser un lugar nuevo tengan en cuenta que tiene mucha demanda pero la fila se mueve rápido así que no desesperen ❤️

Volvería?? Obvio que volvería porque el lugar es tan lindo, las bebidas son deliciosas y los vasitos son demasiado cutes como para ir una sola vez🙈

Boba Bombs 💣 from @sweetstems.co

We got these boba bombs for our friends on their birthday. Our friends love bubbletea, so we thought this would be something cool for them to try out! All of the boba bombs look absolutely beautiful 😍 

The flavours we tried out
* Vietnamese Coffee
* Black Sesame
* Taro
* Matcha Pocky
* Strawberry Pocky
* Fresh Strawberry
* Fresh Mango

All of the boba bombs are covered in white chocolate, so it’s on the sweeter side. The boba bombs comes with the choice of add on’s (pearls, grass jelly, lychee jelly, strawberry jelly, mango jelly, and juicy pearls).

Thai Milk Tea or "Cha Thai"  is one of the most popular drinks in Thailand and you can find Thai tea in most cafes and restaurants in Thailand. 🌻

The price per cup is a start at 15 bath which is less than 50p.👍

Thai milk tea is made from Ceylon tea which is rich with antioxidants. The flavour is sweet and woody aroma. 

Thai milk tea normally served cold as we know Thailand is a hot country we all love cold drink. 

Have a try and you will love it.

📍The Tiny Shop - New Era Square, Sheffield

I’ve legit walked past this place hundreds of times over the past few years, constantly like ‘I’ll go in another time’ and then just... Didn’t 😅

My mum and I had to do some waiting around for my sister in law today, so I finally had time to go in 👀

I got the black sugar milk tea with tapioca (which, by the way, is my new favourite bubble tea. I’ve tried SO MANY bubble tea shops and Chatime had my heart for so long. But this is insanely good) and the popcorn chicken from their street food menu, since my dumbass didn’t have breakfast 😅

They do a bunch of different street foods so it’s great to go to for like a bubble tea and a snack, though I’m excited to try some of their main dishes 👀 17/10 will go back 🤤

Beary Bubbles is restocked on my shop! 
[read more]

Please purchase this design on my shop only! 
.
Ever since this design was made, it’s been bootlegged so many times. The bootlegs have appeared in malls and shops in multiple countries as well as conventions and night markets. It was even used as an ad on Facebook promoting Alibaba lol.... This design can ONLY be purchased legitimately on my etsy or shop website, nowhere else.

Recently it is also being sold on multiple Etsy stores for a super low price. Many makers have been purchasing these and then reselling as other things such as earrings and necklaces. If you are a maker or reseller, please do your research before purchasing stock, its your responsibility to know thoroughly where your items come from. These sales directly impact me as we sell on the same platform, but their stores sell for cheaper or have a wider audience. Most buyers would probably buy from the cheaper shop :/

I’ve always just submitted DMCAs to these shops but recently I’ve received a string of counter notices for my copyright strikes. Thats crazy because all of my designs are original and my own. Etsy does not side with small creators. It seems the only way to rebuttal is to take them to court within 10
days. That’s costly and difficult and the time frame is too small! This means my Etsy shop will likely be dinged yet their bootlegs get to stay up! 
Thank you everyone for informing me of bootlegs you see. It is really helpful to have eyes everywhere ❤️

TLDR; Please please do not purchase bootlegs!!!! If you own a shop which purchases stock or materials, you have to do your research. Every item was created by somebody, not knowing isn’t an excuse!

📍 Birmingham, @ Hey Sugar by Chinatown
🌟 8.5/10 

Has any one else been feeling a little demotivated recently? Ordering some bubble tea puts me in a real goood mood 🤤 

Like most big boba companies, Hey Sugar originates from Taiwan. They began as a small store expanding to over 1000 worldwide! There are 3 stores currently in the UK; @heysugarbirmingham, @heysugarleicester and London. The Birmingham and Leicester branch both have a small bakery inside of the store, whereas the London branch just has bubble tea. 

Before the opening of the first Hey Sugar, the founder travelled almost all over Taiwan trying to source only the best ingredients for their store. Their search of the highest quality of fresh milk to first class teas, lead to their very success. 

The aromas when you first walk into Hey Sugar will make you reminisce the days where you were 3 feet tall walking into your grandparents kitchen! It smells sweet, fragrant then a whiff of baked goods hits you. 

If you are ever in the area, I can promise you that it's worth a try! Or if you don't like boba, it's still worth a walk into store to check out their bakery or desserts. 

These two are my go-to orders that I ALWAYS get without fail, every single time! Ice cream milk black tea, 25% sugar with their golden boba. I love a drink that has a good depth of tea and it isn't too sweet. This drink consists of a LOT of black tea, a scoop of vanilla icecream and their golden boba which are cooked in brown sugar. 

My other favourite is the passionfruit yakult with 25% sugar, coconut jelly cubes and golden boba 🥰 This drink might look odd and sound strange, but hand on my heart it is SUPER delicious, sweet yet tangy and refreshing - perfect for any day of the year! 

I always get my drinks either cold or with 30% ice. Regardless of the weather even when I'm outside and it's 2°C, you won't ever catch me with a hot bubble tea 😂

One of the most popular questions during our last Q&A was if we want to do more international travel. And the answer is HECK YES! As soon as we can safely fly all around the world, we will be visiting as many new places as possible.

But in the meantime, we decided to get a taste of other countries, but from Austin! We went on an international food tour and had so much fun trying some of our favorite international foods, like this amazing crème brûlée dirty boba from @fengchaaustin, as well as some cuisines that were brand new to us, like Ethiopian food! 🧋🧆

We hope this vlog can transport your taste buds abroad! (Warning: do not watch hungry!)

🚨 Bubble Tea Lovers 🧋This one is for you @pyochai 🥳 

PYO Chai is not your average Bubble Tea Shop. They are a fusion of authentic Taiwanese Bubble Tea and South Asian flavors. Here at PYO Chai, they not only respect the origins of Bubble Tea; but have infused it to take on a new cultural context.

PYO Chai 🧋 
📍 100 Covert Ave, Stewart Manor, NY 11530

——
Mango Kulfi Milk Tea 
Falooda Kulfi Milk Tea

——
Yes, It’s a halal bubble tea spot. And honesty it is a vibe. Imagine just being with your friends and relaxing while having amazing artwork, around you to look at. PYO Chai even plays Bollywood music, so you know it’s going to be a good time. Thank you so much for inviting me to taste test. I love the fusion bubble tea concept. I’m definitely coming back inshaAllah. The decoration is beautiful and the staff are really friendly @mera_naamkhan @iamsaqyerr ❤️ The menu is attached so feel free to check it out. 

Stay tuned guys it’s opening soon 😍 and to stay updated follow @pyochai too.

Cold Press Coffee เย็นๆหอมๆชื่นใจมาเเล้วจ้า. วันนี้เเอดมินจะขอเเนะนำความรู้เกี่ยวกับ Cold Press Coffee  ให้ทุกคนได้รับรู้กันจ้า. 

  Cold press coffee คือ กาเเฟที่สกัดด้วยความเย็นจากกระบวนการ การบีบอัดของน้ำเเรงดันสูง โดยไม่ผ่านกระบวนการที่ทำให้เกิดความร้อน เเละกาแฟจะถูกสกัดออกมาเป็นน้ำกาแฟ  ซึ่งจะเป็นเป็นฟองที่เนื้อละเอียดมากๆ เเต่ยังคงความเข้มข้นของคาเฟอีน เเละความหอมกรุ่นของกาเเฟ ไม่ต่างจากการดื่มกาแฟที่เราสกัดจากความร้อน 

 
  ไม่พอไปกว่านั้น Cold Press Coffee ของเรา ยังเป็นเจ้าเเรกที่นำกาแฟมาสกัดจากความเย็นด้วยเครื่องเฉพาะตัวที่มีเเค่ร้านเราร้านเดียวเท่านั้น!!!! 

  ฟองนุ่มๆที่เราเห็นนั้นไม่ใช่นมนะคะ เเต่มันคือครีมม่าที่เกิดจากการบีบอัดจากเครื่อง cold press ซึ่งลูกค้าบางท่านอาจจะคิดว่า เป็นนมรึเปล่า เเต่จริงๆเเล้วไม่ใช่นมน๊าาาา น้องเค้าคือครีมม่าค่าาา 

  เป็นยังไงกันบ้างคะทุกคน ได้ความรู้ใหม่ๆเกี่ยวกับ cold press ไปเเล้ว  อย่าลืมเเวลามาสั่ง cold press coffee กับเรานะคะ 

  อุปซ์🤭🤭 เเต่ถ้าจะให้ดี เเนะนำให้ขึ้นมาทานที่ร้านเราดีกว่า ลูกค้าจะได้เห็นวิธีการทำของเรา จะทำให้ฟินส์มากกว่าเดิมไปอีกจ้า. 

  ร้านเราอยู่ที่ตึก PS Tower ชั้น33 ชื่อร้าน D Cubic coffee&Teaน๊าาาาาา รีบๆมากันนะคะ พวกเรารออยู่จ้า

🧋Was feeling some warm boba on this chilly day…so I treated myself to some at Tea Moment!
I’m so glad I finally got to try it! 

This small boba shop is hidden in the plaza right across from campus, where The Spot is located. Their menu is extensive, with interesting drinks like blue sky milk tea, oreo milk tea, and slushies. They also have a variety of rice rolls for under $5.

💕I always like to try the classic items when I try a new place so I went for the bubble milk tea ($4.25 for the hot option), and I was impressed! It came with bubbles and I liked the consistency of their bubbles- chewy and slightly firm; the bubbles in warm drinks can get slightly too soft but these held their firmness. I got 50% sugar, which was just the right amount of sweetness for me.
For the cold drinks, they seem to put less ice in so that there is more drink to be enjoyed.

🚙 Parking is definitely difficult if you do not have a neighborhood decal, so weekends or weeknights would probably be the best time to go if you are driving there. Also, they do not have outdoor seating but have some tables in the indoor area.
 
📚 If you are on campus, this place would be perfect for a study break!
Follow @teamomentdrinks for more updates!

上次 #望春鳳（Mong Chun Fong）跟上時事議題後，這次開啟 #奶茶聯盟 戰線，首先登場的是 #共緬之（無英文名）和 #泰桑哩（Sonny Cha Thai），也因為近來緬甸局勢而注意到緬甸有奶茶，冷熱口感還有明顯差異！

共緬之的緬語名稱လက်ဖက်ရည်中譯就是緬甸奶茶，是個2020年才開業的緬甸奶茶手搖杯品牌，飲品冰度可以調整，奶茶甜度都固定，冰緬甸奶茶較凸顯奶味，口感滑順，熱的就是茶味很重，若不愛茶味重者可能會覺得澀。

沒想到緬甸也產茶，主要是在和中國雲南相鄰的撣邦，所以緬甸茶喝起來有點像普洱茶，仰光紅茶這個品項可調甜度，微糖喝起來像無糖，茶味也較不澀，同時感受茶香，不過甜度固定的奶茶也沒想像中的超甜。

共緬之有款粉紅奶茶，是加了蛇皮果糖漿的奶茶，喝起來有像是草莓但又不是的味道，還有很多食用色素吧，調製出來的飲品比奶茶色澤要深，其實沒有粉紅，不過糖漿本身真的是豔麗桃紅，這就要點印度冰才看得出。

印度冰看名字就知與印度有關，因為印度和緬甸都曾被英國殖民，當時全部劃為英屬印度，這個由印度人帶入的甜品之後被緬甸人改良，只要是緬甸人都會吃，但不是每家都會做，與摩摩渣渣的不同是加鮮奶。

印度冰是西米露、碎冰、綠色的香草果凍、布丁和冰淇淋組成，還要加上鮮豔的蛇皮果糖漿，喝的時候要先搖一下，讓整杯變成均勻粉紅色，不過這杯主要就是吃料了，跟台灣珍奶差在沒有粉圓和芋圓。

至於泰國奶茶的茶底主要是錫蘭紅茶或當地改良的阿薩姆紅茶特別種Bai Miang，最知名的是用手標茶沖泡，手標茶是由林姓華裔（Lim Meng Kee）創立的茶葉品牌，而能泡出特別的橘色，主要是有食用色素啦～

泰桑哩有加鮮奶和奶精泡的2種奶茶，都會加煉乳，冰塊甜度可調，但道地的泰國鮮奶當然要又冰又甜，加鮮奶的選項比較像是台灣改良版，另外還有手標茶的玫瑰花茶，當然加鮮奶或奶精粉就是玫瑰奶茶囉！

How lovely is my bubble teas in this snowy view?? I got my fave Peach Green Tea with tapioca & Honey Green Tea for my sis who loves bubble tea too. We also ordered their warm & soft bubble waffles for my niece (wish I could eat it but contains dairy). Thank you Gong Cha for the safe delivery of my fave & refreshing bubble teas as I love continuing my support to local bubble tea shops in Toronto. With the warmer weather on the way, it means more refreshing & cold bubble teas delivery ahead...😋 Check out Gong Cha 2 satisfy your bubble tea cravings!! 🍑🥭🍓🌸🌷☀️❄

💭 How is it already March? A year ago, the pandemic hit BC and social distancing measures were put in place. What have we learned?

I learned that we can still build connections while physically apart.

Celebrations can still be had, just need a little bit of creativity.

I learned to listen to my own voice that used to be drowned out in the busy crowds and endless to-do lists.

I learned to rest my body and my mind, enjoy the present and find the joy in the simple ordinary moments.

I learned more about the city I live in, the local shops and restaurants and how to support them.

1 year later, we are still in this pandemic we thought would be over by now. If you feel a bit discouraged, that’s ok, I have been feeling that way too. But let’s not lose hope! This too shall pass!

Thinking abt getting food? "Jus(t) do it" ✔️

Thank you for 2k y’all! Thank you for all your support! 😊

Did you know that @jusfruitcanada & @a_cafeyyc have collaborated to form @jusfruit_acafe ! They offer Korean street food and boba!

I had the Korean corn dog with cheese (& w/ sugar), and it was so good! I love that it wasn't too oily, I'm sensitive to stuff like that so I was super happy! I also love how big it was. The cheese helped me finally do a successful cheese pull ahaha. The only thing was that the hot dog itself was overcooked (it was pretty hard to bite into). The Bulgogi Kimbap was also really good, I haven't had a lot of kimbap so I don't have much to compare it to tho. The Tteokbokki was definitely spicy and the rice noodles were loonngggg, I've never seen them served that long before. It was also a good dish!

For boba we got the Brown Sugar Milk Tea and the JusMango (w/ boba). The Brown Sugar Milk Tea wasn't that sweet, which really surprised me. I think it might be the least sweet brown sugar drink I've tried. The Mango boba had fresh mango on the top, and the drink itself was refreshing. 

Thank you to @bebetteryyc & @jusfruit_acafe for having me! #hosted

Location: JusFruit x A-Cafe Downtown (1324 10 Ave SW)
Food: Potato Corn Dog w/ Cheese, Bulgogi Kimbap, Tteokbokki (not shown), Brown Sugar Milk Tea, JusMango w/ boba

Gong Cha // Peachtree Corners // tea taster 1

Earl grey milk tea w/ boba

🍵Tea: 7/10 the tea taste was good!! It’s on the milkier tasting side (similar to ding tea’s oolong milk tea) but I lowkey like that and you can still taste the tea

🍵Boba: 7/10 the boba tasted good and it was chewy but I think some were borderline a little too hard but overall good

🍵Sweetness: below average — I got less sugar and it was a little too unsweet, could’ve gotten full sugar 

🍵Overall: 7/10 it was good, would probably get full sugar for this drink next time and I think I prefer earl grey from other tea places but Id come back for the oolong!!

Мне кажется, многие стали забывать о самом простом правиле и базе любых человеческих отношений — «о вкусах не спорят». 

Мне непонятна связь между «я люблю что-то» и осуждением или критикой, которые могут последовать со стороны другого человека.

 Осуждение вообще не несёт в себе ничего, оно не имеет никакого значения, но его все равно проговаривают вслух, чтобы специально задеть. Критика уместна только в случае, если увлечение/интерес угрожает обществу или самому человеку. И то, она должна быть объективной, а не основанной на «А Я ТАК НЕ ДУМАЮ». 

Иногда это доходит до абсурда из разряда: кто любит БАБЛ ЧАЙ, тот тп.  Второе...может быть, но какая связь?#bubbletea

TAPIOCA PEARLS! 
I've been missing going out to the bubble tea shop and getting bubble tea since covid began so ended up finding out how to make it at home from scratch. Turns out tapioca pearls only need dark brown sugar, tapioca starch and water! Made the pearls with muscovado sugar then cooked it in a light brown sugar syrup until thickened. There's often talk about different bad chemicals going into some tapioca pearls outside but when you make it at home, you know all the ingredients going into it! Making it at home isn't that hard either, makes for a great at home activity plus they come out with a really great QQ texture. Put it into any tea or smoothie you like and enjoy! 😋

Fundraisers like this help keep these community organizations alive and well so they can continue doing the important work for ALL of our community!

Throughout the last few years, I have seen several bubble tea shops come up with their variations of boba with several items we have grew up enjoying.

If you ask my mother of how she feels about White Rabbit Candy, she will go on a lecture about it from it being a childhood classic in Hong Kong.

In case some of you have not tried it, White Rabbit Candy is milk-based candy similar to nougat which melts into a milky taste after a few bits.

If you're a milk-based bubble tea connoisseur, I can assure you white rabbit 🐇  candy is one of those novelties that actually works well in boba!

In the spirit of #BubbleTeaDay, I encourage you all to visit @panntea_toronto to try their White Rabbit Milk Tea with Egg Pudding! The subtle sweetness of the pudding pairs perfectly with every sip of the white rabbit based milk tea!

If you so happen to be a frequent visitor of Pann Tea, consider getting one of their VIP cards for a 12% off every drink you order!

Be sure to hop on over as I can promise you will not regret ordering this!

I’m always down for alcohol infused anything lol. From bourbon chocolates to wine ice creams, so when I found out that Chaplus released a whiskey flavoured bubble tea series, I had to try!

They also have a black truffles series but that might be a little too adventurous for me at the moment.

This is my entry for the #artandboba_dtiys made by @artandboba and propably the redraw that was the most challenging for me, as the (beautiful) original drawing is completly different to my style and I had so much fun to try to redraw it in my style🥤❤ 

I don't know why, but she somehow seems super bitchy now 🤣 

As usual: the gold and the big black parts are made with Eddings (@edding_de ) and the lines are drawn with @staedtler 's Pigmentliners

Please swipe for the original as well as for a short video to see the golden shimmer 💛⭐

Hope you guys like it ❣

Dies ist mein Beitrag für das ArtandBoba_Dtiys von ArtandBoba und wahrscheinlich das Redraw, das für mich die größte Herausforderung war, da das (wunderschöne) Original komplett anders ist im Vergleich zu meinem Stil und ich hatte beim Malen viel Spaß  meinen Stil reinzubringen 🥤❤

Aus irgendwelchen Gründen sieht sie jetzt super bitchy aus 🤣

Wie immer: das Gold und die großen schwarzen Flächen sind mit Edding gezogen und die Lines mit dem Staedtler Pigmentliner Set

Wenn ihr swiped (gibt es dafür ein schöneres  deutsches Wort?) seht ihr das Original und ein kurzes Video vom goldenen Schimmer 💛⭐

Ich hoffe euch gefällt es ❣

CHICAGO RESTAURANT REVIEW: @hellojasmine.us boba tea 

🧋the fact that there’s a boba emoji brings me great joy in sharing this spot!
🧋locations in both Lincoln Park armitage area and Chinatown 
🧋we ordered the oolong boba tea and brown sugar boba tea and both were so flavorful. These are the most popular flavors
🧋pro tip: don’t mess with the sugar %. Get it as is. I learned this the hard way my first time here and got stuck with a fairly bland tea (otherwise it’s delicious!!)
🧋the ordering system is so easy - you can do pickups from an online order. They also have a huge touchscreen ordering system in the store, which is super easy to use

📍The Yunique Tea - Markham, Ontario

I had seen @teahutsf Sesame Mochi Milk tea on Instagram and I knew I had to try it! I liked how the mochi came in a little bag so that it was easy to make sure they didn’t fall. You can choose your tea base (black, green, oolong) and I chose to add boba as well. It cost me $7 after I added boba (50cents) so if you need a treat yourself day, I would check this place out!! I recommend twisting your mochi in the foam at the top of the drink for a more delicious taste and experience!!

MUÍ [pronouns: mui6] 
In Cantonese we have nine tones. That’s why it sounds like we are singing when we talk. 
The number behind the pronunciation, is the tone for every word. 
MUÍ stands for younger sister in Cantonese.

Hi everyone!! I know, its an unannounced review but i hope you still like it.

I went to @yoyofreshtea with my boyfriend (he got the same drink) on monday. As you can see in the background, i went to yoyo in "de markthal". I've visited this one particular place a lot of times and ive never been disappointed. They recently moved to a new lot in the markthal. One that's way bigger. I got this drink before but not for myself so now i got it for myself to try and i loved it!!
--------♡--------------------------♡--------------------------♡--------
🌺N: Strawberry mint, large. The strawberry mint includes strawberry syrup, green jasmine tea, mint leaves and a slice of lime. I didnt go for extra boba. I loved this tea. Its sweet and a little bit sour from the lime. The price was €4,20 for a large tea. I'd definitely go here again and i recommend you go here too!!

Entre les murs de son restaurant étoilé Quinsou, le chef Antonin Bonnet concocte une évasion en Corée du Sud, meilleur remède à l’immobilisme ambiant. Mamibaba, d’après le surnom de Jina, sa femme originaire de Jeju, une île au sud du pays des matins calmes, propose une cuisine voyageuse. Le hot-dog, aujourd’hui remplacé par le burger du même nom et à la même recette, rassemble une saucisse aux herbes cévenole, moitié porc, moitié blettes, badigeonnée d’une mayonnaise gochujang, camouflée sous du kimchi, adoucie avec un ketchup de pomme et drapée de tranches fines de radis marinés au vinaigre. C’est à la fois explosif, réconfortant et addictif. Et attendez de voir la soupe de ravioles de porc ou le chou à la crème au thé vert… Le périple ne devrait pas être trop douloureux.⁣

Okay, been addicted to Cha Tuk Chak these days 😅 I guess you guys noticed that on my stories hahaha
Anyway, I am also addicted with their Ube cheesecake~ I love how good it is! It is definitely my reco too all of you! Is a must-try indeed! ☺️💖 For their thai milktea cheesecake, this is my mom's fave that's why I bought it for her~ it's definitely the definition of real thai tea so if you're looking for that authentic taste of thai milktea, go for their thai milktea and with the cheesecake helps the drink more enjoyable and creamier! ☺️ And as usual the oreo cheesecake won't be avoided as this is the fave of my brothers hahaha typical taste from boys, they always order this hahaha and yes, I also recommend this especially for the first-timers! Their oreo cheesecake is superb! Plus, Cha tuk chak is very generous with their cheesecake! 💖💖💖 definitely, you won't regret it! 😊💗

This drink was recommended this by the owner at the @gongcha.eastgardens store and I don’t regret getting it 😀 This drink is lit! Better than the taro milk tea in my opinion! 🙌🙌🙌

There was a strong coconut flavour and was generally very smooth and had a constant rooty flavour from the taro 🤤 But I would’ve preferred a stronger taro flavour, the coconut flavour was a tad too strong… 😅

The pearls were cooked to perfection, and even in this super cold drink; the pearls did not harden all that much, still super chewy and squishy like they’re meant to be! 😮

It’s super refreshing and if you’re getting tired of normal pearl milk tea, I would recommend this drink 😁🥰

📍Taicha - Irvine, CA

📸: Uji Matcha Smoothie + boba / Super Peach Jasmine Green Tea 

So my default request is always “half sugar, light ice” whenever I order tea from boba places. That was a mistake here, only because they actually curb their amount of sugar given. So half sugar of an already small amount here = virtually none! Doin’ it right if you ask me. Also, their tea is STRONG. They told me afterwards they steep their tea longer than most places and yes you can taste the quality, but you can also taste the bitterness! (I like that - I know most people don’t.) The barista was more than happy to remake my drink for me when it still wasn’t to my liking, even though I told her she could just add more sugar 😅 She didn’t have to do that! 

So just remember if you normally go half sugar at most boba places, no request needed here! 

What sets this place apart is that there are REAL, WHOLE JASMINE FLOWERS in the Super Peach Jasmine! There are also little pieces of peach jelly and this drink was just a lot of fun in the jasmine + jelly textures! 🍑🌸 Swipe for a closeup!

The Uji Matcha Smoothie didn’t have nearly a strong enough matcha flavor to me, but my bf liked it. (Then again he doesn’t rly like matcha, sooo). It was more milky than tea-like, which I’m not a fan of. But the boba was super chewy and good! And overall we were both very happy with this place! 🧋✨
☯︎ Opposites attract. Comment 🖤 or 🤍 for your favorite

Finally got around to trying @tigersugar.usa’s Black Sugar 🧋 Popcorn 🍿! I ate the whole bag in one night because it was too good 🙃 I thought it was just going to taste like caramel but the brown sugar boba flavor actually comes through at the end!! I haven’t really had much sweet popcorn and didn’t know what to expect and now my expectations for the next sweet popcorn are too high because of these 😂 I mostly have salted butter popcorn 🍿 at the movies and they make my mouth reeeeally dry but for some reason these didn’t? 😂 maybe it’s placebo cus I think I’m drinking boba Lolol. And also... I mean... it’s just puffed corn 🌽 and corn is a vegetable so this is a healthy obsession right 😳😳 ANywAys, highly recommend this snack! I got these at a Chinese supermarket when picking up groceries for my mom, but I know they have these in store and online!! 
~
Tiger Sugar Black Sugar Popcorn 🍿 
Size: 7.05 oz/200 g
Price: $6.99 
Rating: 9/10 😍

Wow, this place is an absolute treat! @boba.cutea.az is the only boba place we know that uses traditional Taiwanese tea brewing techniques for their milk teas, and it shows.  Dani and I tried the royal milk tea and the brown sugar milk tea at 75 percent sweetness, respectively.  The tea flavor shows through on both the milk teas but not overpowering the creaminess of the milk, as a well balanced milk tea should be! At this point, I would like to note that Boba Cutea only uses organic milk and cream for their drinks (no powders here, sorry to the lactose intolerant community), which Dani and I prefer since it doesn’t leave an unpleasant aftertaste after you finish the drink.  Our drinks came with brown sugar boba as a default and it was perfect! I highly recommend Boba Cutea, and the owner Gary was very kind and informative when it comes to helping us understand his tea and shop. He clearly is passionate and driven to get the highest quality ingredients. This discovery is a win for us! -Lj

Tea Top // Doraville // tea taster 1

Darjeeling milk tea w/ boba

🍵Tea: 8/10 tea taste was similar to sun moon lake milk tea or just a regular black milk tea, was very good!! Don’t think I’d get again just because I prefer their earl grey milk tea but I would def recommend it if you’re craving more of a typical black milk tea taste 

🍵Boba: 9/10 their boba is always spot on, I like slightly chewier boba but not too hard so tea top always hit the spot for me

🍵Sweetness: average — I get less sugar and that’s perfect for me, the sweetness level can be a little fickle here?? Haha sometimes less sugar can be too unsweet and sometimes it’s perfect!!

🍵Overall: 8/10 please give tea top a try if you haven’t been here!! 8/10 because it was just slightly watered down and I was just craving earl grey 😂 but it was still good!!

Tea taster 2: 9/10 this is a personal favorite of mine!!! 💯💯

@machimachi_canada recently opened on Robson Street and I was so excited to try it out since I didn’t get to when I was in Taiwan! Arrived an hour before the store opened to line up, since yesterday was the last day of the grand opening and to get one of their free tote bag/cup holder! 🤩 
 
P I C T U R E D: 
🍓 Fresh Strawberry Latte with Panna Cotta • 8.10
🍡 Mochi Cream Foam Black Tea • 6.20 
 
I love how cute and unique their bottles are (although quite pricey). The strawberry latte was creamy and refreshing. They don’t allow you to adjust the sugar level but I didn’t find it overly sweet at all. The mochi cream foam black tea is customizable, and I went with lite sugar which I thought was perfect. They suggest to microwave the mochi for 5-10 secs before dipping it into the drink to enjoy!
 
📍 1194 Robson Street, Vancouver BC

Discovered this lil joint because of#burpplebeyond but i’ll DEFO be back even without!! 🥰@steepedteabar serves up some QUALITY👌🏻 drinks and i loved how they all tasted so natural and well made- we had:

🍓𝑺𝑻𝑹𝑨𝑾𝑩𝑬𝑹𝑹𝒀 𝑩𝑨𝑺𝑰𝑳 𝑶𝑶𝑳𝑶𝑵𝑮 (6.60)
They use Mediterranean sweet basil which is floral and less licorice-like than the more common Thai basil. Paired with tart strawberry puree, it tastes like a summer day! My sis loved this!!
🤤𝕋𝕒𝕤𝕥𝕚𝕟𝕖𝕤𝕤 7/10

🌹𝑹𝑶𝑺𝑬 𝑳𝒀𝑪𝑯𝑬𝑬 𝑹𝑨𝑺𝑷𝑩𝑬𝑹𝑹𝒀 (7.20) 
This was sweet, fruity, floral and milkier than I expected- the soft flavours of the rose and lychee were offset by the tartness of the raspberry! Kinda like bundung but gentler and more natural with a twist??? HAHAHA
🤤𝕋𝕒𝕤𝕥𝕚𝕟𝕖𝕤𝕤 7/10

🫐𝑳𝑨𝑽𝑬𝑵𝑫𝑬𝑹 𝑩𝑳𝑼𝑬𝑩𝑬𝑹𝑹𝒀 (6.60)
You can tell that its brewed fresh, and paired with blueberry puree. The Lavender was super fragrant and floral but it didn’t taste too much like perfume, as it was mellowed out by the sweet fruity blueberries. 
🤤𝕋𝕒𝕤𝕥𝕚𝕟𝕖𝕤𝕤 7/10

🍵𝑴𝑨𝑻𝑪𝑯𝑨 𝑳𝑨𝑻𝑻𝑬 (6.30) 
This is one of the few places i’ve seen that whisks their matcha to order, rather than pre-made. You can definitely taste the difference- this is one of the better matcha lattes i’ve had!! Its the earthy umami type without getting too astringent- loved it!! Not too sweet and not too milky either, just how i like it! 
🍵𝕄𝕒𝕥𝕔𝕙𝕒𝕟𝕖𝕤𝕤 7.5/10
🤤𝕋𝕒𝕤𝕥𝕚𝕟𝕖𝕤𝕤 7.5/10

You can tell that @steepedteabar puts a lot of thought and effort into wach and every one of their drinks, and I greatly appreciated that🥺!! Just a stones throw from Bugis Junction, they also serve some bakes by @flor_patisserie so pop by for a chill pill if you’re in the area!!

Stopped to try a new boba tea place (it's a food truck) that the daughter and I saw a few days ago. I was pleased to learn that they were able to make me a caffeine free taro milk tea, which none of the established tea houses can seem to figure out. It was the best bubble tea that I have had in a long time. It was flavorful and also smooth and creamy. They use real milk and nort powdered creamer, so it didn't separate or look gross. If you like boba tea and are in the North Houston area, check out Infuzion Bubble Tea Bar! They have 3 locations - Cypress, Porter, and Spring.

Hi Friends👋🏻

We are to-TEA-lly in love with bubble tea🤩 But our love for @gongchacanada keeps getting bigger and bigger and we are not mad about it🤩 

As you all know we’ve been working through the gong cha menu slowly but surely😉 For this visit we ordered two items under their Oreo brownie series🤩 Pictured are their ✨OREO BROWNIE TARO LATTE✨ 
& ✨OREO BROWNIE BLACK TEA LATTE✨ Both drinks we added pearl, because lets be real, bubble tea ISNT complete without it😜 Both flavours were AMAZING🙌🏻 The topped Oreo bits and milk foam made the drinks 10x better👏🏻 

Our fave of the two was the taro latte because it reminded us of our childhood🥺 Even without topping of the brownie bits and foam the drink alone you can’t go wrong, a classic👌🏻

Support this business y’all🙌🏻 All the drinks we’ve tried (and we’ve tried a lot) from gong cha, none of them were disappointing or any less than delicious👏🏻

Anaïs, my 11 years old daughter, loves Bubble tea. She makes it all by herself. Here her recipe:
In a big glass, mix water and 1/3 cup of instant boba, until blended. In a pan, boiled water then add the tapioca bubbles. Take them out when they float on the top of the boiling water. Rinse them with cold water for 20 seconds and add them to the blend. Optional : you can add honey or syrup to the tapioca bubbles. Enjoy 😊

Another at home version of one of my favourite drinks from London - @yifangtea.uk wintermelon tea with green tea jelly 😍 

I ordered some green tea jelly powder a little while ago and decided I would try my hand at making an at home version of YiFang Tea's wintermelon with green tea jelly. It was a pretty straightforward recipe, using my standard fruit tea recipe for the wintermelon tea and making the green tea jelly according to the instructions which meant I had a quick, easy and refreshing drink! Of course, I had to put it in my @mybobamate bottle (to make me feel like I've actually been somewhere other than my garden recently 😂) It tasted great and took me back to London 😍

Since I had a lot of green tea mix I also decided to do my own version of the jelly bubble tea I've seen with a green tea jelly with nata de coco (swipe to the third pic to see how it turned out!) 💕 I was so impressed it actually came out of the plastic cup in one piece 😂 

I hope everyone has a great week! I've got lots of exciting content coming up that I can't wait to share with you guys 💕

I’ve been in Seattle with my sister. My sister has lived in Seattle for several years and before that she has lived in Africa and Connecticut. This is the first time I have come to visit her. She was switching jobs, so she has time between the last job ending and the new one beginning. She’s recently received the covid vaccine and while I have antibodies we took advantage of this time to come together. It’s been lovely, we have hiked, snow shoed, gotten lots of yummy carry out, got bubble tea from a food truck. Loving my time here with her but can’t wait to get back to you at the truck! See you soon! 
Peace love and boba 
✌️ 💕 🧋
