📍The Whale Tea, Queensway
@thewhaleteauk kindly invited us to try some of their new bubble tea flavours and the drinks are honestly AMAZING! They have 300 outlets around the world including Australia, Canada, Singapore, Malaysia, China, Taiwan and finally London! 🎉

We tried:
-‘Winter Melon’ is winter melon tea with peach resin, crystal balls and coconut jelly. This drink is so refreshing and we love all the different flavours and textures that came together so well in one drink!🍈 
-‘Sweety Potato’ is milk and smashed purple sweet potato with brown sugar boba. We were so excited to try this drink as we have never heard of anything like this before, it did not disappoint - milky with delicious chunks!! So unique and looks cool too, a must try!🍠
-‘Flaming Whale’ is fresh milk with salty cheese cream on top and brown sugar boba. We sipped the cheese foam first, then mixed the whole drink which gave it a sweet and salty taste, it was so good!!🐋 
-‘Matcha Dalgona Coffee’ is matcha latte and smooth coffee foam on top with brown sugar boba. So impressed with this drink because you can actually taste the coffee and the matcha and it’s so creamy! We’ve tried similar drinks before where the matcha overpowers the drink but this one was perfect!🍵
-‘Perfect Mango’ is rich mango juice with milk, mango bits and crystal balls and grapefruit. This reminded us of Mango Lassi, it was thick, creamy and perfect for all mango lovers like us!🥭

We loved every drink! They were all so unique and we would order each of them again! 😍 We highly recommend trying out @thewhaleteauk, they have such a large variety of drinks to choose from as well as vegan options! @thewhaleteauk is open for takeaway and available on @deliveroo and @ubereats_uk. We will definitely be visiting for our bubble tea fix!🧋 Thank you to Joan for the unparalleled level of customer service and explaining every drink! Check them out and let us know your thoughts! 😋

Happy Monday! I was inspired by the bubble tea stickers that I wanted to make a favorite childhood Hmong dessert that we called Nab Vam. Nab Vam (naa-va) is a sweet coconut dessert drink that has colorful tapioca pearls, cendol, and other toppings mixed in it and is commonly found across Southeast Asia. Of course, I had to put a corny saying with it! I can’t wait to release the sticker and matching card with it! Be on the look out for the release.
.
I’ll nab vam (never) stop loving you!

Introducing our: MILK TEA STORIES Body lotion!✨This special body gel is inspired by the natural ingredients of milk tea and hydrates your skin while creating a quickly absorbed smoothened layer. It is suitable for every skin type and a long term companion because you just need a small amount to nourish your skin.

In a time where we aren’t able to travel like we once did, I realized that milk tea became not only my personal signature smell for traveling. I hope this product can help you overcome wanderlust and creating nostalgic moments on your skin.✨🧴

Thanks for everyone who helped us transporting our ideas into reality! Launching MILK TEA STORIES has been a wonderful journey and has given me the feeling of meeting my fav cities again!🌆❤️

黑芝麻控看這裡！💗💗 他們家的必點的黑芝麻糊厚鮮奶真的是必點！滿滿一大半杯的黑芝麻糊，是採用手炒黑芝麻粒及帶有穀物感的糙米新鮮做成的！一拿到就聞到超香的芝麻香氣，如果喝起來的黑芝麻味再更濃一點就更好了。記得搖一搖把黑芝麻糊融入到燕麥奶裡面再喝喔。還有！「☕️400次咖啡」這個在韓國之前超爆紅的飲料不用在家裡辛苦的打，這家在菜單上就可以直接點了！和一般不一樣的就是他們可以把飲料基底升級燕麥奶喔，然後上面在放上打發的綿密咖啡奶泡，口感不僅滑順還帶了更濃郁燕麥香來提味！推薦來試看看升級後更～好喝的特別燕麥奶飲品吧，共有三款黑芝麻糊厚鮮奶，土豆花生厚鮮奶和400次咖啡！😋

Calling all black sesame lovers!! I recently found a place to try black sesame drink in Hsinzhu. The drink comes with almost half a cup full of freshly made thick black sesame paste, made from fresh black sesame seeds and brown rice grains. You can instantly smell the black sesame scent when you get the drink, but I just wished that the flavour was a bit more stronger! Remember to shake it up to mix it well before drinking~ also, they also have the super super popular drink Dalgona coffee on their menu too! We upgraded the drink to change the base to oatmilk base, which paired the whipped coffee foam even better, the oat milk flavour was subtle and smooth and added a little twist to the regular dalgona coffee. Recommend to try out this place if you are looking for fresh drink options with oat milk and unique drinks for a nice treat!

DONUT MINI COKLAT CARAMEL

BENTUK BOLEH MINI TAPI RASA DAN UNTUNGNYA NENDANG BANGET !

Jangan cuma nontonin Odading Mang Oleh lg viral itu. Ayo bebikin resep ala dapur OmaEmi ini Donut Mini Coklat Caramel. Aktivitas simple ini bisa jadi obat anti stress dan bosan karena hasilnya sangat berfaedah menyenangkan org lain membuat perut kenyang dan potensial untuk peluang usaha 

Bahan Bahan
200g Tepung Terigu
50 g Gula Pasir 
1 Telur
50 ml air 
1sdt Baking Powder
Minyak Goreng secukupnya 

TABURAN 
40 gr BUBUK MINUMAN OMAEMI CARAMEL 
20 gr Gula Kastor

CARA MEMBUAT
1. Masukan tepung terigu, telur, gula, telur aduk hingga rata, lalu tuang air aduk2 hingga kalis 
2. Bentuk bulat2 kecil 
3. Goreng dlm minyak panas dengan api sedang. Bolak balik donut agar tidak gosong dan seteleh kecoklatan angkat
4. Tusuk donut dengan tusukan sate
5. Campurkan Bubukan Minuman OmaEmi Caramel dengan gula kastor setelah itu tabur kan dengan donut mini ini
6. Donut Mini ueenakk banget begitu di gigit rasa manis coklat caramelnya berpadu dengan adonan yg empuk, lembut, kenyal dan wangi caramel. Makan satu tusuk ga cukup 

Peluang usaha yg sangat menjanjikan pundi2 keuangan! Yg terpenting kreativitas dan upaya jgn sampai terhenti karena kebutuhan kita gak pernah berhenti

Ikan hiu makan tomat 
Jangan tunggu jualan donut 
Rasa istimewa karena pakai bubuk minuman omaemi rasa coklat caramel

Yuu Japanese Tapas 🍜 Dine Out Vancouver 

This is probably the cheapest dine out deal you'll find LOL considering how a bowl of ramen is usually $15 already. Still working on my noodle pull game, I know it's weak 🥺

3 Course Lunch ($15) 
Starter:
• Hokkaido Curry Croquette - deep fried hokkaido potato cake
•Takoyaki - octopus balls with okonomiyaki sauce, mayo, bonita flakes 

Entree: 
• Tonkotsu Ramen - aburi chashu, Ajitsuke egg, corn, bamboo shoots, bean sprout, seaweed, green onion in homemade rich tonkotsu broth ! ( side note: I asked for no bean sprouts 😂)

Dessert: 
• Boba Anmitsu - matcha ice cream with peach, pearls and red bean 

They were also having a 2 for 1 drinks promo! So we got : 
• Peachy lemonade with pearls 
• Hokkadio milk tea with pearls 
Both drinks for $6.75 

The Croquette was pretty good, it had a mild curry taste and corn inside; really appreciated that they  presented it nicely too! For such a cheap price, I thought they would just throw it on the plate 😂

Takoyaki was mediocre, nothing too special that makes it stand out. 

The Tonkotsu ramen was also decent, not the best ramen ever. But considering the price, it's really not bad at all. The broth was not too salty which I liked and had good flavour too!

Boba Anmitsu was good! The red bean was a tad too sweet for me  but good matcha ice cream. Everything worked well together. 

Overall, I think @yuujapanesetapas 's dine out menu is worth it! I think you get more than what you pay for and there's still a week left for you to try it ! 😊 the food is mediocre  but for that price point, I ain't complaining !They got really busy today, so I recommend making reservations if you can!

⭐️ Thai Brown Sugar Pearl Milk Tea [$6.50]
⭐️ Brown Sugar Pearl Milk [$6.50]
⭐️ Brown Sugar Earl Grey w/ Pearls [$5.00 excluding topping]
⭐️ Jasmine Macchiato w/ Pearls [$6.25 excluding topping]

Rating: 9/10

Review:

𝘽𝙍𝙊𝙒𝙉 𝙎𝙐𝙂𝘼𝙍 𝙀𝘼𝙍𝙇 𝙂𝙍𝙀𝙔 𝙒/ 𝙋𝙀𝘼𝙍𝙇𝙎- If you are an Earl Grey fan, you will love this drink! It is one of Jenjudan’s signature drinks. Paired with their chewy brown sugar pearls, it surely is a refreshing drink! I recommend 30% sugar because the pearls itself are already sweet.

𝙃𝙊𝙏 𝙅𝘼𝙎𝙈𝙄𝙉𝙀 𝙈𝘼𝘾𝘾𝙃𝙄𝘼𝙏𝙊 𝙒/ 𝙋𝙀𝘼𝙍𝙇𝙎- Topped with a cheese foam, this hot drink is warm and cozy for a chilly winter day. The jasmine tea is light and 0% sugar does the job if brown sugar pearls are added.

At the Granville location, you can bring your old receipt from a purchase there and choose one drink from a selection of three drinks for $3.50! Currently, the three drink selection in February are Brown Sugar Earl Grey, Passionfruit Green Tea, and Winter Melon Tea Latte.

Jenjudan Granville Location is right next door to Red Star Seafood Restaurant, which makes it super convenient to grab a bubble tea after dimsum! Go check them out!

📍8278 Granville St, Vancouver, BC V6P 4Z4

Dzisiejsze super fotki dostałam od naszej przeuroczej Ambasadorki z Warszawy @leszczynska_03 ❤️! Przy okazji mam temat przewodni, bo Lena zrobiła sesję pośród Street Artu, może takiego mniej atrakcyjnego wizualnie, bardziej "dzikiego" graffiti, ale niewątpliwie jest to dziedzina sztuki, która obejmuje dzieła tworzone w przestrzeni publicznej, zwykle mające charakter bezprawnej ingerencji 😁... Ale mamy w Warszawie także mnóstwo pięknych murali i świetnych wlepek, tak naprawdę jak zaczniecie się rozglądać po mieście (każdym!!!) to zobaczycie, że żyjecie wśród mniejszej, lub większej, ale sztuki 😉! Ważnym prekursorem Street Artu w USA, gdzie wszystko się zaczęło, był Jean-Michel Basquiat, artysta i przyjaciel Andy'ego Warhol'a, który w latach 70. ozdabiał mury Nowego Jorku różnymi prowokacyjnymi napisami. Teraz najbardziej popularnym TWÓRCĄ na świecie jest znany Wam zapewne BANKSY ❤️! Mamy tu jakiś fanów Street Artu 😁?

Pamiętajcie, że już wkrótce pojawi się w naszych sklepach stacjonarnych nowy SMAK MIESIĄCA, więc jak nie piliście jeszcze CHERRY CHERRY LADY to koniecznie spróbujcie, bo zostało Wam już tylko kilka dni 🥤!!!

Możecie je zamówić również w butelce przez nasz sklep internetowy:

You-gurt to grow healthy bones. I want to be a strong bear when I grow up! 🧸🍼💪

Daddy took me to try @chewgurtyummy for their yogourt drink. We chose the dragonfruit and the purple rice yoghurt. They are both mild and slightly sweet tasting. These drink starts at $6.50 for the equivalent of a regular sized bubble tea, the dragonfruit being the most expensive one at $8.🧋

It is a healthy alternative to bubble tea but pricier. That’s why I think it’s a good idea to drink this instead of boba, but not in additional to my monthly boba treat. And truthfully I do enjoy making my yogurt (protein) smoothies at home hehe. 

Btw, how do you guys spell yogourt? There is a British English, American and Canadian/French way! For me I tend to write yogourt! 🤯

Well, it isn't alcohol, but it'll suffice I guess.
Boba, Bobar. Clever. Boba, bubble tea, the quintessential Asian drink, whatever the hell you call it, can be found at Bobar, a boba tea place found in Elk Grove. Which is, admittingly, strange considering Elk Grove is almost like a desolate wasteland of boredom and suburban mediocrity.
I don't usually drink boba. I often think it's overhyped, but maybe that's because my allegiance is to Western coffee. But, boba is indeed pretty good, and here at Bobar, they do it pretty fine. Serving coffee, smoothies, milk tea, and other stuff, I got some matcha milk tea. It came in these neat cups that were the size of a McDonald's medium Coke, which I find pretty adorable and neat branding.
It was bitterish, but I got matcha so I couldn't complain, and it came out pretty well actually. My buddy got some sweet melon thingy which I found good, I should try it sometime. It was a neat establishment, very busy from the looks of it. I'd probably hang out here if it weren't Covid, as it does seem like a friendly, cozy, and bustling business.
There are few boba places I'd ever actually go to, but it seems Bobar has managed to put itself on my radar. So check it out, my young padawans. Tell me what you think.

Hey Bobalovers! ¿Sabías que el Bubbletea se ha convertido en una experiencia gastronómica universal?
.
Así es. Luego de sus primeros pasos en Taiwán, el Bubbletea o Té de burbujas conquistó todo el continente asiático haciéndose parte de su cultura, para después saltar a Europa y América, estando seguramente presente en todos los continentes. 
.
Por eso puedes disfrutar de un delicioso bubbletea en Taipei, Tokio, Seúl, pero también en Barcelona, París, Nueva York ¡y ahora en Caracas!
.
Y seguimos esta semana llevándote la experiencia del Bubbletea con  ZenBobba, en la modalidad delivery y pickup, recuerda que también puedes ordenar por @somosdingo y por la App de @yummy.vzla .
.
Y te adelantamos una súper noticia.... ¡La próxima semana podrás vivir la experiencia ZenBobba en el Bobatruck en la Plaza Castellana junto a @ftcaracaspower !
.

Wannabe Bubble Tea is here! Step 1: Boil water, add tea and condensed milk, steep over night (or a few hours until cold) in fridge. Step 2: Boil water and add boba (buy on Amazon or in Asian grocers), cook for 20 minutes until pearls float. Boba should be chewy in center but, soft on outside. Rinse boba in cold water to stop cooking. Step 3: Add cooked boba back into pot with abit of remaining boiled water, add brown sugar, let simmer till sticky syrup forms. Step 4: Assemble from bottom to top...boba, ice, tea. Feel free to add any toppings like whipped cream if your feeling gluttonous. FYI, cooked boba can be refrigerated or frozen, just reheat with sugar water to revive. Enjoy boba lovers! #boba #foodblog #bubbletea #foodstagram #foodie #wheninquarantine #drinks @lipton

@happylemonliverpool are a bubble tea shop based in Myrtle Parade (perfect for uni students!) They are an international franchise with over 1,000 branches all over the world. At Happy Lemon, each drink uses the best quality tea combined with naturally fresh lemon to make every single cup the yummiest drinks in the world.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🧋 As each drink is made to order, you can customise each drink to your taste from how much sugar or ice, the toppings or if you prefer it hot or cold. There really is a drink for everyone! ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
🕙 Opening hours: Mon-Sun, 12:30pm to 8:30pm⁣⁣
⁣⁣
💭 What we ordered and our thoughts:⁣⁣
▪️ Brown Sugar Boba Milk Tea - The tapioca pearls (the bubbles) are soaked in brown sugar. This is our personal fave, as simple variation to the classic bubble tea and forever our go to order 🤤⁣⁣
▪️ Milk tea with Oreo and puff cream - this was a really enjoyable alternative with yummy bits of Oreos. Our only regret is not getting tapioca pearls in this too! 😅⁣⁣
▪️ Boba mocaccino milk tea - for any coffee lover (like us!) this was phenomenal ⁣⁣
▪️ Dragonfruit slush with cream foam - sweet, fruity and very aesthetically pleasing. We can’t wait for sunnier days as this would be perfect! 💜⁣⁣
▪️ Matcha milk tea with tiramisu salted cheese - easy choice for matcha lovers. I think this would be even better served hot. The tiramisu salted cheese isn’t as funky as it sounds either 🧀 ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Have you had bubble tea before? If so, what’s your go-to order? ⁣⁣
⁣⁣

Yesterday my bf and I drove all the way to @panntea_toronto to redeem my free drinks that I won from @markhamfoodie 😋 Before coming here, I was eyeing their creme brûlée drinks so I had to try one of them! 

I got the creme brûlée cake milk tea with 50% sugar and it was BOMB 👌🏼 It was my first time trying creme brûlée in bbt and I’m ALL for it 😍 I also liked the cake pieces in it which added more texture to the drink 🍰 Although the tapioca was nice and chewy, I found it just a lil hard but that’s cuz I prefer my tapioca super soft haha 🙈 

I also got 3 creme brûlée milk teas w/ tapioca for my bf and his parents and it was really good as well! I think it’s basically the same as the drink that I got but minus the cake pieces 😜

I also wanted to mention the guy who was serving me was so kind! The VIP card I won was $25 and although I ordered 4 drinks which was a little bit over, he let it slide (maybe it’s because I had to wait until all the other drinks were done haha). Also, I last minute added tapioca to the cake drink which he did free of charge as well! So yea, just wanted to say that the service was sooo good hehe 😌💖

Overall, I would highly recommend this place for those of you who haven’t tried! Even though it’s super far from my house, I’d definitely come back here again. Thanks for having me @panntea_toronto 🥰

🧋: creme brûlée milk tea w/ tapioca (9/10)

Ingredients:

1 tablespoon water
1 1/2 teaspoons brown sugar
1 tablespoon tapioca starch
Green tea, for serving

Steps:

1. To a sauce pot, add water and brown sugar; bring to a boil. Stir until all the sugar has dissolved. Turn off heat.

2. In a bowl, add tapioca starch and 1 1/2 teaspoons of the hot sugar water and stir to combine. Remove from bowl and knead until a smooth pliable dough forms.

3. Divide dough into smaller pieces, and roll out into thin cylinders. Cut off tiny pieces, and roll into tiny balls. Bring remaining sugar water in pot to a boil. Add tapioca pearls, stirring to ensure they do not stick. Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, or until soft but still chewy in the center. Remove from pot with a slotted spoon, transfer to a bowl and cover with sugar water. The tapioca pearls will become translucent. Pour tapioca into a glass and top with your favorite tea or juice.
